[2] Rabies, feline, human exposure - Maryland
Date: 24 April 2012
Source: The Republic.com [edited]
http://www.therepublic.com/view/story/b885d61d1d12472cb504f03dd613ee83/MD--Rabid-Cat/

Rabid cat found in Cecil County; 5 scratched by animal in Port Deposit
----------------------------------
Cecil County [Maryland] health officials say rabies has been found in a sickly stray cat that scratched 5 people in downtown Port Deposit. The 5 people were scratched Friday. The cat was captured and euthanized at a veterinarian's office and tested.

The 5 people have been urged to seek treatment.

The cat is described as a small- to medium-sized yellow tabby. Anyone exposed to the animal in the past 10 days should go to an emergency room. Officials say this is the first domestic animal that has tested positive in Cecil County this year. The previous cases were in 4 raccoons and a skunk.
--
